      Mozambique kidnappings and crisis
          </h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-image border-radius="10px" padding="10px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com/email/images/mozambique-neglected-crisis-nrc-jan-egeland.jpg" alt="Jan Egeland, secretary general of the Norwegian Refugee Council, called the situation in northern Mozambique one of the world's neglected crises" href="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com" />
        <mj-text padding="0px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#A9A7AF">
          <p style="font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.2; color: #A9A7AF;"><i>
          Jan Egeland, secretary general of the Norwegian Refugee Council, called the situation in northern Mozambique one of the world's neglected crises. Credits: Tim Cowley</i></p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
        <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
       In Mozambique‚Äôs Cabo Delgado province, the Islamist group <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-25-jun-25-spotlight-h1-1-al-shabab-has-abducted" target="_blank">al-Shabab has abducted</a> at least 120 children since early 2025. This group is linked to the Islamic State but not to Somalia‚Äôs al-Shabab, which is another terror group with the same name. They force children into labor, combat, and marriages.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
     The region also witnessed a <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-25-jun-25-spotlight-h1-2-rise-in-violence" target="_blank">rise in violence</a> since 2017. This conflict has displaced 1.4Mn people and killed over 6,000. The Mozambican government depends on foreign military aid to fight the insurgency. Natural disasters, such as Cyclone Chido and recent tornadoes, have exacerbated living conditions.</p>
         <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
      Climate issues and hunger are pushing many toward crisis. The Norwegian Refugee Council reports that over 5Mn people face severe hunger, with nearly 1Mn in emergencies. Aid efforts are lagging due to global neglect and the <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-25-jun-25-spotlight-h1-3-us-aid-cutoff" target="_blank">US aid cutoff</a> under the Trump administration. </p>
        </mj-text>
