          <h2 style="font-size:24px;line-height:1.2;font-weight:500; margin-top:2px !important">
     Securing minerals, containing China
       </h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
        <p style="font-size:18px;line-height:1.5;">
         <strong>
        Summary: The US shifts its focus to Africa to secure minerals and to contain China‚Äôs military growth.  </strong>
         </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
           The United States is not adequately prepared for a more <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-25-jun-25-analysis-h1-6-challenging-global-environment" target="_blank">challenging global environment</a>. A group of nations, led by China and Russia, aims to weaken the US-led global framework in favor of a multipolar system. China is ramping up its military growth and bolstering its defense industry to enhance its global power and reduce US influence. 
          </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
          To counter this, the US has shifted its focus toward Africa. The African continent holds one-third of the world‚Äôs known mineral reserves, including 80% of platinum and chromium, 47% of cobalt, and 21% of graphite. The US Geological Survey identifies 50 critical minerals, with Africa containing thirty-two of them. However, the US lacks a strong or concise strategy to utilize these resources or counter the influence of China and Russia on the continent. 
          </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
          Experts maintain the notion that if the US assists African nations in developing mineral processing capabilities, it can help partners retain economic value. This strategy promotes self-reliance in defense and secures vital supply chains. The United States should outline its defense priorities, identify essential African resources, and provide recommendations to enhance US-Africa cooperation in an era of global competition. 
          </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
          Read the full report <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-25-jun-25-analysis-h1-7-here" target="_blank">here</a>. 
          </p>
