      <mj-spacer height="10px"/>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;padding-top:4px;padding-bottom:6px;">
           <strong>üá∞üá≠ Cambodia - Halts Thai imports.</strong> 
           Tensions between Cambodia and Thailand have surged after a Cambodian soldier was killed in a disputed border area. In response, Cambodia will halt all fuel imports from Thailand. A leaked conversation between Thai PM Paetongtarn and Cambodia‚Äôs Hun Sen worsened the fallout, initiating political turmoil in Thailand (<a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-25-jun-25-worldwide-8-southeast-asian-clashes" target="_blank">Southeast Asian clashes</a>).
          </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;padding-bottom:6px;">
           <strong>üá∫üá∏ United States - Judge Blocks Trump.</strong> 
           A federal judge has indefinitely blocked a Trump administration decree aimed at preventing Harvard University from enrolling international students. Judge Allison Burroughs ruled the proclamation violated constitutional rights and was part of a retaliatory campaign. She criticized efforts to suppress academic liberty and diverse viewpoints (<a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-25-jun-25-worldwide-9-study-abroad-back-on" target="_blank">study abroad back on</a>).
          </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;padding-bottom:6px;">
           <strong>üá©üá™ Germany - Skilled immigrants at a high.</strong> 
           A report from the Rockwool Foundation Berlin shows that 32.1% of non-EU migrants in the EU held a university degree in 2024, up from 30.9% in 2023. Germany mirrored this trend, with an increase from 29.4% to 31.1%. Experts say that better utilization of migrants' skills could significantly boost EU economic growth (<a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-25-jun-25-worldwide-10-the-full-study" target="_blank">the full study</a>).
          </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;padding-bottom:6px;">
          <strong>üá™üá∫ European Union - Considering measures.</strong> 
          The EU is considering measures against Israel over human rights violations in Gaza. While some member states advocate for suspending agreements or imposing arms embargoes, others oppose taking such intense measures. A review is underway, and further steps may be taken in July (<a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-25-jun-25-worldwide-11-divided-opinions" target="_blank">divided opinions</a>).
          </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;padding-bottom:6px;">
          <strong>üáµüáπ Portugal - Tightens citizenship rules.</strong> 
          Portugal will tighten its immigration and citizenship laws, doubling the residency requirement to 10 years for most foreigners and seven for those from Portuguese-speaking nations. Applicants must demonstrate cultural integration and a clean criminal record (<a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-25-jun-25-worldwide-12-cracking-down" target="_blank">cracking down</a>).
          </p>
